{{term|1= Abacus |content= [[Abacus (architecture)|Abacus]] }}
{{defn|1= A flat slab forming the uppermost member or division of the capital of a column. }}

{{term|1= Accolade |content= [[Accolade (architecture)|Accolade]] }}
{{defn|1= A sculptural embellishment of an arch. }}

{{term|1=Aisle  |content= [[Aisle]] }}
{{defn|1=Subsidiary space alongside the body of a building, separated from it by columns, piers, or posts. }}

{{term|1=Ante-choir  |content= [[Ante-choir]] }}
{{defn|1=The space enclosed in a church between the outer gate or railing of the [[rood screen]] and the door of the screen.}}

{{term|1= Apron |content= [[Apron (architecture)|Apron]]  }}
{{defn|no=1 |1= raised panel below a window or wall monument or tablet.}}
{{defn|no=2 |1= open portion of a marine terminal immediately adjacent to a vessel berth, used in the direct transfer of cargo between the vessel and the terminal.}}
{{defn|no=3 |1= [[concrete]] slab immediately outside a vehicular door or passageway used to limit the wear on asphalt paving due to repetitive turning movements or heavy loads.}}

{{term|1= Apse |content= [[Apse]] }}
{{defn|1= Vaulted semicircular or polygonal end of a chancel or chapel.  That portion of a church, usually Christian, beyond the "crossing" and opposite the nave.  In some churches, the choir is seated in this space. }}

{{term|1= Araeosystyle |content= [[Araeosystyle]] }}
{{defn|1=An architectural term applied to a [[colonnade]], in which the [[intercolumniation]] is alternately wide and narrow.}}

{{term|1= Arcade |content= [[Arcade (architecture)|Arcade]] }}
{{defn|1= Passage or walkway covered over by a succession of [[arch]]es or [[Vault (architecture)|vault]]s supported by [[column]]s.  Blind arcade or arcading: the same applied to the wall surface.}}

{{term|1= Arch |content= [[Arch]] }}
{{defn|1=A curved structure capable of [[Span (architecture)|spanning]] a space while supporting significant weight. }}

{{term|1= Architrave |content= [[Architrave]] }}
{{defn|1=Formalized lintel, the lowest member of the classical entablature. Also the molded frame of a door or window (often borrowing the profile of a classical architrave). }}

{{term|1= Arris |content= [[Arris]] }}
{{defn|1=Sharp edge where two surfaces meet at an angle such as the corner of a square column or shaft. }}

{{term|1= Arrowslit |content= [[Arrowslit]] }}
{{defn|1= A thin vertical aperture in a fortification through which an archer can launch arrows. }}

{{term|1= Articulation |content= [[Articulation (architecture)|Articulation]] }}
{{defn|1=Articulation is the manner or method of jointing parts such that each part is clear and distinct in relation to the others, even though joined. }}

{{term|1= Ashlar |content= [[Ashlar]] }}
{{defn|1=Masonry of large blocks cut with even faces and square edges. }}

{{term|1= Atlas |content= [[Atlas (architecture)|Atlas]]}}
{{defn|1=A support sculpted in the form of a man, which may take the place of a column, a pier or a pilaster. }}

{{term|1= Atrium |content= [[Atrium (architecture)|Atrium]] }}
{{defn|1=(plural: atria) Inner court of a Roman or C20 house; in a multi-story building, a toplit covered court rising through all stories. }}

{{term|1= Attic |content= [[Attic]] }}
{{defn|1= Small top story within a roof above the uppermost ceiling. The story above the main [[entablature]] of a classical [[façade]].}}
